{
  "title": "Vector Fundamentals",
  "summary": "Definition of vectors, magnitude, direction, triangle rule for addition, Cartesian components, unit vectors i j k, position vectors, and basic vector operations.",
  "widget_type": "variables",
  "position": 1,
  "is_published": true,
  "content_html": "<style>\n.formula-box{background:#0f172a;border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 20px;margin:10px 0;font-family:monospace;font-size:.97em;color:#f1f5f9;text-align:center}\n.note-box{background:#1a2e1a;border-left:4px solid #22c55e;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0;color:#bbf7d0;font-size:.93em}\n.def-box{background:#1e293b;border-left:4px solid #38bdf8;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0}\n.warn-box{background:#2d1f1f;border-left:4px solid #ef4444;border-radius:4px;padding:10px 16px;margin:10px 0;color:#fca5a5}\n.ex-box{background:#ffffff;border:1px solid rgba(15,118,110,.18);border-radius:8px;padding:18px;margin:10px 0;color:#111827}\n.vec{font-weight:700;color:#0f766e;font-family:Cambria Math,Cambria,serif}\n.calc-row{display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin:6px 0;font-family:monospace;font-size:.93em;align-items:center}\n.step-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:10px 0;font-size:.9em}\n.step-table td,.step-table th{border:1px solid #334155;padding:6px 10px;color:#e2e8f0;font-family:monospace}\n.step-table th{background:#1e293b;color:#7dd3fc}\n.mat{display:inline-grid;border-left:3px solid #94a3b8;border-right:3px solid #94a3b8;padding:6px 12px;gap:4px 14px;border-radius:2px;background:#1e293b;vertical-align:middle}\n.mat td{text-align:right;font-family:monospace;font-size:.93em;color:#e2e8f0;min-width:20px}\n</style>\n<h3>2.1 The Geometric Approach</h3>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 2.1 — Vector:</strong> A quantity with both <strong>magnitude</strong> (size) and <strong>direction</strong>. Represented graphically as an arrow. Examples: velocity, force, acceleration.</div>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 2.2 — Initial & Terminal points:</strong> Vector AB starts at point A (initial) and ends at B (terminal).</div>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 2.3 — Magnitude:</strong> Written |AB|, |<b>a</b>|, or simply a. The length of the arrow.</div>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 2.4 — Equal vectors:</strong> Two vectors are equal if they have the <strong>same magnitude and same direction</strong> — they may have different positions in space.</div>\n\n<h4>Vector Addition — Triangle Rule</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Definition 2.5 — Triangle rule:</strong> Place vectors head-to-tail. The sum <b>c</b> = <b>a</b> + <b>b</b> connects the tail of <b>a</b> to the head of <b>b</b>.</div>\n\n<div class=\"ex-box vector-example\">\n  <div class=\"vector-example-title\">\n    <strong>Example 2.1 — Ship navigation</strong>\n    <span>Ship speed in still water = 30 km/h north. Current = 20 km/h east.</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"calculation-grid\">\n    <div class=\"calc-card\">\n      <div class=\"calc-label\">(a) Pointing north</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-equation\">α = arctan(<span class=\"math-frac\"><span>20</span><span>30</span></span>) = arctan(<span class=\"math-frac\"><span>2</span><span>3</span></span>)</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-result\">33.7° east of north</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"calc-card\">\n      <div class=\"calc-label\">(b) Travel due north</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-equation\">ψ = arcsin(<span class=\"math-frac\"><span>20</span><span>30</span></span>) = arcsin(<span class=\"math-frac\"><span>2</span><span>3</span></span>)</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-result\">41.8° west of north</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"calc-card\">\n      <div class=\"calc-label\">(c) Land speed</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-equation\">v = √(30² − 20²) = √500</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-result\">22.4 km/h north</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Cartesian Components</h4>\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Unit vectors:</strong> <span class=\"vec\">i</span> (x-axis), <span class=\"vec\">j</span> (y-axis), <span class=\"vec\">k</span> (z-axis) — each has magnitude 1.</div>\n<div class=\"component-formulas\">\n  <div><span>Any vector</span><strong>a = a₁i + a₂j + a₃k</strong></div>\n  <div><span>Magnitude</span><strong>|a| = √(a₁² + a₂² + a₃²)</strong></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"ex-box vector-example\">\n  <div class=\"vector-example-title\">\n    <strong>Example — Cartesian operations</strong>\n    <span><b>a</b> = 3<b>i</b> + 2<b>j</b> − <b>k</b>, <b>b</b> = <b>i</b> − 4<b>j</b> + 2<b>k</b></span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"calculation-grid\">\n    <div class=\"calc-card\">\n      <div class=\"calc-label\">Addition</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-equation\">a + b = (3 + 1)i + (2 − 4)j + (−1 + 2)k</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-result\">4i − 2j + k</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"calc-card\">\n      <div class=\"calc-label\">Magnitude</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-equation\">|a| = √(3² + 2² + (−1)²) = √(9 + 4 + 1) = √14</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-result\">≈ 3.742</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"calc-card\">\n      <div class=\"calc-label\">Unit vector</div>\n      <div class=\"calc-equation\">â = <span class=\"math-frac\"><span>a</span><span>|a|</span></span> = <span class=\"math-frac\"><span>3i + 2j − k</span><span>√14</span></span></div>\n      <div class=\"calc-result\">direction of a</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<h4>Scalar Multiplication and Key Properties</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li><b>a</b> + <b>b</b> = <b>b</b> + <b>a</b> (commutative)</li>\n  <li>(<b>a</b> + <b>b</b>) + <b>c</b> = <b>a</b> + (<b>b</b> + <b>c</b>) (associative)</li>\n  <li>k(<b>a</b> + <b>b</b>) = k<b>a</b> + k<b>b</b> (distributive)</li>\n  <li><b>a</b> − <b>b</b> = <b>a</b> + (−<b>b</b>) = <b>a</b> + (−1)<b>b</b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"def-box\"><strong>Position vector:</strong> Vector from origin O to point P = (x,y,z) is <b>OP</b> = x<b>i</b> + y<b>j</b> + z<b>k</b>.<br>\nVector from A=(a₁,a₂,a₃) to B=(b₁,b₂,b₃): <b>AB</b> = (b₁−a₁)<b>i</b> + (b₂−a₂)<b>j</b> + (b₃−a₃)<b>k</b></div>\n",
